Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/hasTerritorialApplicability
Object: Relates a data set release to it's territorial applicability.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/AverageType
Object: Used to express the method of averaging used for data set releases covering a time period rather than a point in time (date).

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/endOn
Object: Relates a temporal coverage of a period to the end date of that period.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/DataPoint
Object: A specific data point in a statistics release version. A measure for a given population at a point in time or averaged over an interval.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/TerritorialApplicability
Object: The territorial applicability of a data set release. Allows us to say that a given release of a data set contains data from a given source (organisation) for a given place e.g. a constituency. Sources may change between releases.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/
Object: Statistical series ontology for UK Parliament. Primarily aimed at modelling statistical information around places. Deprecated in favour of RDF Data Cube.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/updateFrequency
Object: Relates a data set to any textual account of its update frequency.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/hasUnit
Object: Relates a data set to the unit in which the data is counted e.g. GBP.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/boundBy
Object: Relates a population (of people, residences, businesses etc) to a geographic area.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/People
Object: A population of people in a place. This might be all people resident or over 70s resident or people in receipt of Universal Credit etc.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/averagedOverPeriodAs
Object: Relates a temporal coverage to any means of averaging employed on the data.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/Businesses
Object: A population of businesses in a place. This might be all registered businesses or business in a certain industrial sector.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/countPer
Object: Relates a data set to the period over which the data points in the data set are counted e.g. average wage per week.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/DataSet
Object: A data set e.g. age profiles by constituency over time.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/Period
Object: The period over which a measurement is counted e.g. wages per week.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/inPlace
Object: Relates territorial applicability to a geographic area.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/fromSource
Object: Relates territorial applicability to a data source organisation.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/temporalCoverage
Object: Relates a data set release to the time period or point in time the data was gathered.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/onDate
Object: Relates a temporal coverage of a day to that date.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/startOn
Object: Relates a temporal coverage of a period to the start date of that period.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/caveatText
Object: Relates a data set to any caveat text accompanying it.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/releasedOn
Object: Relates a data set release version to the date on which it was released.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/value
Object: Relates a data point to it's value as an integer.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/releaseVersionOf
Object: Relates a data set release version to a data set release.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/Unit
Object: The unit of measurement for all data points in a stats series e.g. GBP.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/Population
Object: A set of things bounded by a geographical extent. Might be a population of residents, a population of those eligible to vote, a population of small businesses, a population of static caravans, in a constituency etc.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/releaseNotes
Object: Relates a data set release to explanatory notes.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/Place
Object: A place. Any geographical extent. In the case of parliamentary demographic statistics we'll usually be dealing with a constituency area but other places may be needed in the future e.g. local authority areas.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/inDataSetReleaseVersion
Object: Relates a data point to the data set release version it forms part of.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/releaseOf
Object: Relates a data set release to a data set it forms part of.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/DataSetReleaseVersion
Object: A version of a release of a data set. Different versions may be released over time to correct miscalculations etc.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/DataSetRelease
Object: A release of a data set. Different versions may be published over time to correct mistakes.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/measureOf
Object: Relates a data point to a given population.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/Residences
Object: A population of residences in a place. This might be all residences or local authority owned residences etc.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/TemporalCoverage
Object: The period or point in time (date) covered by a statistics release e.g. quarter 1 of 2018 or April 2016. Allows period coverage to vary between releases.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/Source
Object: The source organisation for a given subset of a data set release. Much of the data published by the House of Commons Library originates with the Office of National Statistics but often originates with other organisations for the devolved nations e.g. Northern Ireland Statistics and Research Agency for Northern Ireland. Other data sets originate in government departments.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/stats-series/releaseVersionNotes
Object: Relates a data set release version to explanatory notes.
